{"lemma":"سَبْحَةٌ","slug":"سَبْحَةٌ","root":"س.ب.ح","root_slug":"س-ب-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18666"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"misbaha, rosary"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sub.ħa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18666","headword_ar":"سَبْحَةٌ","root":"sbH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Garments of skins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, accord. to Sh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAHN","text_ar":"سِبَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the pl., signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shirts of skins, for boys:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AO corrupted the word, relating it as written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subojapN","text_ar":"سُبْجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":", and with damm to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whereas this signifies “ a black [garment of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” and a verse cited by him as presenting an ex. of its pl., in its last word, is from a poem of which each verse has for its fundamental rhyme-letter the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":": ISd, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbj","text_ar":"سبج"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAjN","text_ar":"سِبَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ garments of skin, ” and having"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbjp","text_ar":"سبجة"},{"kind":"text","text":"for its sing.; but says that the word with the unpointed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of higher authority; though he also states it, in the same art., to have been corrupted by AO. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [A meaning belonging to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suboHapN","text_ar":"سُبْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(q. v.) is assigned in some copies of the K to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHapN","text_ar":"سَبْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aboHapu","text_ar":"السَّبْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboHapu","text_ar":"سَبْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAbiHN","text_ar":"سَابِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to a horse, or mare, (IAth, TA,) is a proper name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mare, belonging to the Prophet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, K, TA:) and of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another belonging to Jaafar the son of Aboo- Tálib;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or this was"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mare named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoHapu","text_ar":"سَمْحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O:) and of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"another belonging to another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","IAth","TA","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}